
1- Git init - to initialize the empty .git repository

To make the connection of local project to remote repo
use below command
Git remote add origin repo_url

Directory graph

Working Directory   ->     Staging   --> Local directory  --> Remote directory


Git add - to stage the new file
Git reset- if newly file is staged then if you want to delete the file
Git restore - to discard the changes from the staging
Git push -u origin branch_name- to push to remote branch
git add -A - to add all the files to staging area


git add *.java
git add file1.java file2.java -> if you want to stage the multiple files in one go

Git commit -am "commit message" -> if a file is modified and you want to add and commit in one command
